\section{Cash Spending Use Case}
Here is the use case for our MyMoney application.

\medskip
\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{| l | p{6cm} |}
\hline

Use Case ID  & MyMoneyW18COMP354a\\
\hline
Use Case Name  & Cash Spending\\
\hline
Goal/Purpose  & Allow a user to manage his/her cash spending via a desktop application\\
\hline
Actors  & Any User\\
\hline
Pre-Conditions &  User has installed "My Money" desktop application \\
\hline
Post-Conditions & NA \\
\hline
Main Flow & User wants to update his/her expenses.
1. User opens the application and selects the Cash Spending button. 
2. The application displays a table with actual expenses on taxes, tuition, rent, groceries and a button to add other expenses.
3. User clicks on the "Add an expense" button and selects one of the spending's categories.
4. User enters the amount he spent on the selected category.
5. The application stores the value in the expenditure's table. 
\\
\hline
Alternate Flow(s) & NA

\\
\hline
Exception Flow(s) & â€¢ 1. User entered invalid inputs(ex. a string)
   b) The application displays error message, and urges user to fix the input. \\
\hline

\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\end{document}
